@startuml Replication Model
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

title Kafka Replication and Leader-Follower Model

package "Topic: user-events" {
    component "Partition 0" as p0 {
        component "Leader\n(Broker 1)" as leader0 #LightGreen
        component "Replica\n(Broker 2)" as replica0_1
        component "Replica\n(Broker 3)" as replica0_2
    }
    
    component "Partition 1" as p1 {
        component "Replica\n(Broker 1)" as replica1_0
        component "Leader\n(Broker 2)" as leader1 #LightGreen
        component "Replica\n(Broker 3)" as replica1_2
    }
    
    component "Partition 2" as p2 {
        component "Replica\n(Broker 1)" as replica2_0
        component "Replica\n(Broker 2)" as replica2_1
        component "Leader\n(Broker 3)" as leader2 #LightGreen
    }
}

component "Producer" as prod
component "Consumer" as cons

prod --> leader0 : Write message
leader0 --> replica0_1 : Replicate
leader0 --> replica0_2 : Replicate

replica0_1 --> leader0 : Acknowledge (ISR)
replica0_2 --> leader0 : Acknowledge (ISR)

leader0 --> prod : Commit (acks=all)

cons --> leader0 : Read message
cons --> leader1 : Read message
cons --> leader2 : Read message

note right of p0
  **Replication Factor: 3**
  - 1 Leader (handles reads/writes)
  - 2 Followers (replicate data)
  - All in ISR (In-Sync Replicas)
end note

note right of leader0
  **Leader Responsibilities:**
  - Handle all read/write requests
  - Track ISR status
  - Coordinate replication
end note

note right of replica0_1
  **Follower Responsibilities:**
  - Replicate data from leader
  - Become leader if current leader fails
  - Stay in sync with leader
end note

@enduml
